PROJECT: crypto

CURRENT STRUCTURE
- Root launcher: ./start.sh
- Backend: services/backend
- Frontend: services/frontend
- Backend config: services/backend/config.json
- Backend secrets: services/backend/.env
- Runtime files: /tmp/crypto-runtime
- Persistent history: MongoDB

PRIMARY RULES
- Edit service paths, not deleted legacy root paths.
- Do not reintroduce repo-local runtime storage under data/.
- Root start.sh is the main entrypoint.
- services/backend/start.sh is a compatibility wrapper only.
- Frontend history/analytics should rely on MongoDB, not repo JSONL archives.
- Never commit secrets, .env files, runtime files, or caches.

BACKEND HOTSPOTS
- services/backend/src/live_adaptive_trader.py
- services/backend/src/strategy.py
- services/backend/src/trade_engine.py
- services/backend/src/models.py
- services/backend/src/binance_futures_rest.py
- services/backend/src/binance_executor.py
- services/backend/src/config.py

FRONTEND HOTSPOTS
- services/frontend/server.py
- services/frontend/src/*
- services/frontend/index.html

IMPORTANT INVARIANTS
- ClosedTrade.result must match actual pnl direction.
- When TP and SL hit in the same candle, SL wins.
- One open trade at a time unless intentionally changed.
- Event output must remain valid JSON per line.
- original_stop_loss must remain intact for risk accounting.

DEFAULT COMMANDS
- pnpm install
- pnpm lint
- pnpm frontend:dev
- pnpm frontend:build
- ./start.sh --skip-optimize
- cd services/backend && pytest tests/ -v

PERMISSIONS / EXPECTATIONS
- Full local repo access is expected.
- Network may be used when required for the project.
- Prefer direct execution and implementation over planning-only responses.
- Keep changes aligned with the current services architecture.

READ FIRST
- AGENTS.md
- README.md
